beer.beer_description: Like its cousin the Pale Ale, an Amber Ale is primarily characterised by its hopping. And who are we to mess with that? So we went and added multiple parcels of hops in varying combinations using US Cascade and Tasmanian Galaxy. Fancy. The resulting combination if malts delivers a deep amber colour and soft, full palate. Just before it turns sweet the hops rush in, in all their spicy, floral, fruity glory.
